// C2: Acting Components
instance SwingAngleEncoderActuator : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Electromagnet at the end of the hoist used to pick up and release containers, controlled via remote interface for adaptive control mechanisms."
]

instance HorizontalMotorController : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Motor controller for horizontal movement enabling precise positioning of containers along predefined trajectories."
]

instance VerticalMotorController : DTDFVocab:ActingComponent [
    base:desc "Motor controller for vertical movement enabling precise positioning of containers along predefined trajectories."
]

// C3: Physical Sensing Components
instance SwingAngleEncoder : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Measures the swinging motion of suspended containers to ensure stability during transport."
    DTDFVocab:producedData SwingAngleDataTransmitted
]

instance Anemometer : DTDFVocab:SensingComponent [
    base:desc "Measures wind speed which may affect crane operations."
    DTDFVocab:producedData WindSpeedDataTransmitted
]

// C4: Physical-to-Virtual Interaction
instance SwingAngleDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom SwingAngleEncoder
]

instance WindSpeedDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom Anemometer
]

// C10: Models/Data
instance CraneKinematicModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "Parametric CAD-based kinematic model of the gantry crane for trajectory generation and motion control."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo CraneSimulationEnabler, TrajectoryGeneratorEnabler
]

instance CraneGeometricModel : DTDFVocab:Model [
    base:desc "3D CAD model of the crane structure and container pucks for collision detection and visualization."
    DTDFVocab:inputTo GrafanaVisualizationEnabler, ContinuousValidationEnabler
]

instance CraneOperationalData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Time-series data of crane state including positional, kinematic, and dynamic parameters."
    DTDFVocab:fromData CraneStateDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo TimescaleDBEnabler, HistoricalLoggingEnabler
]

instance TrajectoryData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Generated trajectory setpoints and execution logs for crane movement."
    DTDFVocab:fromData TrajectoryExecutionLogDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo TrajectoryGeneratorEnabler, ContinuousValidationEnabler
]

instance WindSpeedData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time wind speed measurements affecting crane operations."
    DTDFVocab:fromData WindSpeedDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ContinuousValidationEnabler
]

instance SwingAngleData : DTDFVocab:Data [
    base:desc "Real-time swinging motion measurements of suspended containers."
    DTDFVocab:fromData SwingAngleDataTransmitted
    DTDFVocab:inputTo ContinuousValidationEnabler
]

// C11: Enablers
instance TimescaleDBEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Hybrid relational/time-series database optimized for high-write throughput (1kHz sensor data) and SQL-based queries for historical analysis."
    DTDFVocab:enables HistoricalDataLoggingService
]

instance MQTTBrokerEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Lightweight publish-subscribe messaging broker facilitating asynchronous signaling between services with low-latency communication."
]

instance GrafanaVisualizationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Customizable dashboards with time-series panels, 3D visualizations, and alerting rules for real-time monitoring."
    DTDFVocab:enables DataVisualizationService
]

instance PythonDevelopmentEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Core logic implementation using Python modules with libraries for MQTT, data processing, and plotting."
]

instance CraneSimulationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Python-based kinematic solver for trajectory planning and simulation of crane movements."
    DTDFVocab:enables TrajectoryGeneratorService, ContinuousValidationService
]

instance TrajectoryGeneratorEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Service for computing optimal actuator inputs based on kinematic model and physical feedback."
    DTDFVocab:enables OptimalControlService
]

instance ContinuousValidationEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Implementation of continuous validation methods comparing predicted vs actual crane states."
    DTDFVocab:enables ContinuousValidationService
]

instance HistoricalLoggingEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Time-series data storage and retrieval for post-mortem analysis and performance benchmarking."
    DTDFVocab:enables HistoricalDataLoggingService
]

instance FaultDetectionEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Data-driven or model-based approaches for identifying deviations from expected crane behavior."
]

instance PhysicalCraneInterfaceEnabler : DTDFVocab:Enabler [
    base:desc "Python program interfacing directly with physical crane controllers for real-time data acquisition."
    DTDFVocab:enables PhysicalCraneInterfaceService
]

// C6: Services
instance PhysicalCraneInterfaceService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Primary data acquisition layer collecting real-time operational data from physical crane controllers."
    DTDFVocab:provides CraneStateDataInsight
]

instance TrajectoryGeneratorService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Generates optimal trajectories for crane movement based on kinematic model and real-time feedback."
    DTDFVocab:provides TrajectoryOptimizationAction
]

instance ContinuousValidationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Real-time synchronization and discrepancy detection between physical and digital twin states."
    DTDFVocab:provides ContinuousValidationInsight
]

instance FaultDetectionService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Anomaly detection and diagnostics for sensor failures, actuator drifts, and kinematic inconsistencies."
    DTDFVocab:provides FaultDetectionInsight
]

instance HistoricalDataLoggingService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Time-series data storage and retrieval for crane operations including sensor readings and actuator commands."
    DTDFVocab:provides HistoricalDataInsight
]

instance DataVisualizationService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Interactive 3D/2D dashboards rendering CAD models synchronized with real-time sensor data."
    DTDFVocab:provides RealTimeVisualizationInsight
]

instance OptimalControlService : DTDFVocab:Service [
    base:desc "Real-time/near-real-time control optimization for trajectory planning and adaptive control policies."
    DTDFVocab:provides AdaptiveControlAction
]

// C17: Insights/Actions
instance CraneStateDataInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Continuous recording of crane's positional, kinematic, and dynamic parameters for real-time monitoring."
]

instance TrajectoryOptimizationAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Computes optimal actuator inputs for energy-efficient motion and collision avoidance."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

instance ContinuousValidationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Real-time comparison of predicted vs actual crane states with distance metrics and threshold-based alerts."
]

instance FaultDetectionInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Identification of sensor failures, actuator drifts, and kinematic inconsistencies with severity classification."
]

instance HistoricalDataInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Structured logs of crane operations for longitudinal trend analysis and performance benchmarking."
]

instance RealTimeVisualizationInsight : DTDFVocab:Insight [
    base:desc "Interactive 3D/2D dashboards highlighting deviations between physical and digital crane states."
]

instance AdaptiveControlAction : DTDFVocab:Action [
    base:desc "Dynamic refinement of control actions based on real-time feedback from physical system."
    DTDFVocab:IsAutomatic true
]

// C1: Environment
instance LabScaleGantryCraneEnvironment : DTDFVocab:Environment [
    base:desc "Controlled laboratory environment with constrained motion ranges, low payload capacity, and deterministic operational conditions."
    base:contains PhysicalCraneComponent, CraneControllerComponent
]

instance PhysicalCraneComponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Scaled-down mechanically functional gantry crane with kinematic motion capabilities for research and educational purposes."
    base:isContainedIn LabScaleGantryCraneEnvironment
]

instance CraneControllerComponent : DTDFVocab:Component [
    base:desc "Embedded or external control hardware/software interfacing with crane actuators to execute commands."
    base:isContainedIn LabScaleGantryCraneEnvironment
]

// Missing DataTransmitted instances for services
instance CraneStateDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom PhysicalCraneInterfaceService
]

instance TrajectoryExecutionLogDataTransmitted : DTDFVocab:DataTransmitted [
    DTDFVocab:producedFrom TrajectoryGeneratorService
]

instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "Control commands originate from the **Human Machine Interface (HMI)**, which forwards operator inputs to the **Control Application**. The **Trajectory Generator Service** computes optimal trajectories (ensuring no residual swinging motion at the end) and transmits these as commands via the **Control Application** to the **Physical Crane Interface**. The **Control Application** validates trajectory feasibility before execution, while the **Continuous Validation Service** monitors real-time trajectory performance by comparing executed paths (via **Physical Crane Interface**) against simulated trajectories (from the **Simulation Service**). Operator notifications are triggered via the **Dashboard** if deviations exceed predefined thresholds. No explicit validation/authentication mechanisms, conflict resolution protocols, or command execution confirmation mechanisms (beyond logging) are documented."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin systems described adopt a **lightweight, ad-hoc orchestration pattern** without reliance on commercial Digital Twin frameworks. The **GreenhouseDT** exemplar employs **InfluxDB (time-series database)**, **ActiveMQ (message broker)**, and **virtual machines** for behavioral adaptation, indicating a **service-oriented architecture (SOA) with loose coupling** between physical (greenhouse) and digital components. The **Air Quality Management** exemplar uses **Microsoft Azure tools** for pipeline implementation, suggesting a **cloud-centric orchestration** with **AutomationML** for model-driven engineering. The **lab-scale gantry crane** (implied in the context) leverages the **C4 Model** for architecture visualization, hinting at a **modular, containerized deployment** with **clear separation of concerns** (e.g., sensor data, control logic, visualization). Coordination mechanisms are **implicitly handled via message brokers (ActiveMQ) or cloud services (Azure)**, with no explicit mention of **orchestration frameworks (e.g., Kubernetes, Apache Camel) or real-time synchronization protocols** (e.g., OPC UA, MQTT)."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin system incorporates a **Continuous Validation Service** that dynamically compares real-time measurements (e.g., Swing Angle Encoder, Anemometer) with simulated trajectories to ensure fidelity. Validation methods are not quantified (e.g., no mention of mean absolute error or other metrics), but the service implies real-time error detection and correction. Uncertainty sources are not explicitly detailed, though environmental factors (e.g., wind speed) and mechanical tolerances (e.g., motor precision) likely contribute. Quality assurance processes are implied by the ad-hoc Digital Twin pipeline, which relies on containerization and virtualization for reproducibility. No prerecorded data or formal verification protocols are mentioned for the Gantry Crane system."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "The system employs **MQTT** as the primary communication protocol for inter-service signaling, leveraging its lightweight publish-subscribe model for asynchronous data exchange. The **Database** (TimescaleDB) uses PostgreSQL’s native protocol for structured data storage and retrieval. No industrial protocols (e.g., Modbus, CAN) or dedicated network infrastructure (e.g., switches, routers) are mentioned; all components are hosted on a **single personal computer**, implying a local, non-distributed architecture. Bandwidth/latency requirements are unspecified, though the **Continuous Validation Service** suggests real-time or near-real-time data flows. Security protocols (e.g., encryption, access controls) are not documented."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The entire system, including the **Digital Twin** (Database, Dashboard, Trajectory Generator, Simulation, and Validation Services) and **Physical Crane Interface**, is deployed on a **single personal computer** via Docker containers. No cloud, edge, or hybrid deployment is referenced; the **Physical Crane** is directly connected to this machine. Computational/storage requirements are unspecified, though TimescaleDB and Grafana imply moderate resource needs. Scalability mechanisms (e.g., horizontal scaling) are absent; the system is designed for local, single-user operation. Availability/reliability assurances are not documented beyond basic containerization."
]

instance horizontal_integration : DTDFVocab:HoriIntegration [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin exemplars demonstrate **limited but domain-specific horizontal integration** with external systems. The **GreenhouseDT** relies on **InfluxDB (time-series storage)** and **ActiveMQ (message broker)** for internal data exchange, with no explicit mention of **interoperability standards (e.g., OPC UA, FDT/DTM)** or enterprise system integration (e.g., ERP, MES). The **Air Quality Management** exemplar uses **AutomationML** for Digital Twin modeling, which is a **standardized engineering data format** for automation systems, enabling **interoperability with PLCs, SCADA, or CAD tools**. It also leverages **Microsoft Azure**, implying integration with **cloud-based analytics or IoT platforms**. The **lab-scale gantry crane** (contextual) does not specify external integrations, but the **C4 Model** suggests potential for **modular extensions** (e.g., linking to warehouse management systems). No dependencies on **third-party Digital Twin frameworks** (e.g., Siemens MindSphere, PTC ThingWorx) are noted, reinforcing an **ad-hoc, domain-isolated approach**."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin exemplars demonstrate **partial standardization** with the following key compliance and interoperability features:
  - **Industry Standards**:
    - **AutomationML**: Explicitly adopted in the **Air Quality Management** exemplar for digital twin modeling, ensuring semantic interoperability with industrial automation systems (e.g., PLCs, SCADA).
    - **No explicit mention** of other standards (e.g., ISO 23247 for Digital Twins, OPC UA for industrial communication) in the provided documents.
  - **Technical Specifications**:
    - **InfluxDB** (time-series database) and **ActiveMQ** (message broker) in **GreenhouseDT** adhere to open-source protocols but lack formal standardization.
    - **Microsoft Azure tools** in the **Air Quality Management** pipeline imply cloud-native compliance (e.g., Azure IoT Hub for device connectivity).
  - **Certification/Compliance Frameworks**: Not explicitly documented in the provided texts.
  - **Interoperability**:
    - **Hardware Agnosticism**: Use of **Raspberry Pi** and **single-board computers** suggests modularity but no standardized hardware interfaces.
    - **Data Exchange**: **ActiveMQ** (JMS protocol) and **AutomationML** (XML-based) enable cross-platform communication, though no mention of **OPC UA** or **MQTT** for IoT interoperability.
    - **Virtualization/Containerization**: Leverages **virtual machines** and implied **Docker/Kubernetes** (via containerization discussion) for deployment consistency but lacks container standards (e.g., CNCF certifications)."
]